        <h1>LeetCode 2126: Destroying Asteroids (C++)</h1>
        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                You are given an integer mass representing the mass of a planet and an array asteroids where
                asteroids[i] is the mass of an asteroid. You can destroy an asteroid if your current mass is greater
                than or equal to its mass. When you destroy an asteroid, you gain its mass. Return true if you can
                destroy all asteroids, or false otherwise.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: mass = 10, asteroids = [3,9,19,5,21]<br>
                Output: true<br>
                Explanation: After destroying the asteroid with mass 3, your mass becomes 13. After destroying the
                asteroid with mass 5, your mass becomes 18. After destroying the asteroid with mass 9, your mass becomes
                27. After destroying the asteroid with mass 19, your mass becomes 46. After destroying the asteroid with
                mass 21, your mass becomes 67. The mission is accomplished.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    bool asteroidsDestroyed(int mass, vector&lt;int&gt;&amp; asteroids) {
        long long m=(long long)mass;
        int n=asteroids.size();
        sort(asteroids.begin(),asteroids.end());
        for(int i=0;i&lt;n;i++)
        {
            if(m&gt;=asteroids[i])
            {
                m+=asteroids[i];
            }
            else
                return false;
        }
        return true;        
    }
};</code></pre>
